'''''South Riding''''' is a [[BBC]] serial in three parts from 2011, based on the 1936 novel ''[[South Riding (novel)|South Riding]]'' by [[Winifred Holtby]]. It is directed by [[Diarmuid Lawrence]] and written by [[Andrew Davies (writer)|Andrew Davies]]. It stars [[Anna Maxwell Martin]], [[David Morrissey]], [[Peter Firth]], [[Douglas Henshall]], [[Penelope Wilton]] and [[John Henshaw]].

The first episode aired on [[BBC One]] and [[BBC HD]] 20 February 2011, the two remaining on the following Sundays. In the United States, it aired on [[Masterpiece (TV series)|PBS's ''Masterpiece'']] in May 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/masterpiece/southriding/index.html |title= South Riding |year= 2011 |publisher= PBS |accessdate= 22 January 2012}}</ref>

